  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200ºC/ 180ºC (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1664279105096-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1664279105096-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1664279105096-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1664279105096-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1664279105096-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 25 min or until the potatoes are golden</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1664279110658-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1664279110658-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1664279110658-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1664279110658-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1664279110658-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>sugar </strong>and cook for 8-9 min or until softened and caramelised</p><p>Once softened, transfer your <strong>caramelised onion </strong>to a small bowl, reserving the pan, with your <strong>chilli relish </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> cold water – this is your <strong>sweet onion chilli relish</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1664279127754-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1664279127754-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1664279127754-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1664279127754-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1664279127754-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is cooking, add your <strong>smoked streaky bacon</strong> to a separate baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!) and put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until golden and crispy</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in 2 batches!</p><p>Dice your <strong>tomato[es]</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and shred finely</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
